text: Palirisa salex is a moth in the family Eupterotidae. It was described by Pugaev and T.T. Du in 2011. It is found in Vietnam., 2011: Palirisa salex sp. nov., a new species from Vietnam (Lepidoptera: Eupterotidae). Tinea 21 (4): 203-213. ==References== Category:Moths described in 2011 Category:Eupterotinae
